                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.51/67.</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Tampico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-07-24T10:00:00-06:41">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 24, 1914, 10 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your July 23, 3 p.m. Proper representations were made several days ago regarding
                    the Christian Brothers. At present the Brothers at the other points named are
                    not yet within the jurisdiction of the Carrancistas but attention has been
                    called to them in accordance with the Department’s instructions.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Silliman</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
